[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Conseslus Kipruto breaks the Olympic record as he wins gold

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Kenyan Conseslus Kipruto won the men's 3,000m steeplechase gold medal in Rio with an Olympic record time.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
The 21-year-old finished in eight minutes 3.28 seconds to edge American Evan Jager into silver. Defending champion Ezekiel Kemboi, 34, took bronze.
